info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Flood Advisory issued September 24 at 7:51AM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CDT TODAY... * WHAT...Urban and small stream flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected. There have been some reports of minor flooding around the Duluth area, and the river gauge along the Knife River suggests that river levels have been rising rapidly through the night. * WHERE...In Minnesota, Lake and St. Louis Counties. * WHEN...Until noon CDT Sunday. * IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas. River or stream flows are elevated. Ponding of water in urban or other areas is occurring or is imminent, especially along the hilly terrain in the Duluth area and along the North Shore. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 745 AM CDT Sunday, Doppler radar and automated rain gauges indicated heavy rain due to thunderstorms. This is causing urban and small stream flooding. Between 1 and 4 inches of rain have fallen. - Additional rainfall amounts of 0.5 to 2 inches are expected over the area today. This additional rain will result in minor flooding. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Superior, Hermantown, Two Harbors, Proctor, French River, Stoney Point, Knife River, City of Rice Lake, Larsmont, Irving, Lakewood Twp, North Shore, Palmers, Lakeside-Lester Park, Morley Hts/Parkview, Congdon Park, Chester Park, East Hillside, Kenwood and Central Hillside. - Flood safety information can be found at www.weather.gov/safety/flood.
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Do not attempt to cross flooded roads in hilly terrain. Find an alternate route.
